# IPL Data Analysis Project

## Overview

This is a beginner-level Data Analysis project created while learning Python libraries such as NumPy, Pandas, and Matplotlib.

The project uses an IPL dataset to perform data analysis and visualization, helping understand how data can be explored and presented using Python.

## Tools and Libraries Used

* Python
* NumPy
* Pandas
* Matplotlib
* Jupyter Notebook

## Project Tasks

* Load and explore the IPL dataset
* Clean and process data
* Perform basic statistical analysis
* Filter and group data using Pandas
* Create visualizations using Matplotlib
* Extract useful insights from the dataset

## Concepts Practiced

* Data Cleaning
* Data Analysis
* Data Manipulation
* Data Visualization
* Working with CSV Files
* Pandas DataFrames
* NumPy Arrays

## Files Included

* `IPL_project.ipynb` – Jupyter Notebook containing the complete analysis
* `IPL.csv` – Dataset used in the project

## Learning Outcome

This project helped me gain practical experience with NumPy, Pandas, and Matplotlib. It improved my understanding of data analysis workflows and working with real-world datasets.

